        <ItemComponent><Armor body_armor="0"/></ItemComponent>
        <Description text="[ASHEN_VIGOUR] The fire in you can be divided. It burns others instead. Right-Right-Down-Down. Twenty days of your life to restore thirty points of health to every ally at your shoulder."/>
    </Item>

    <!-- The Wasting  DRLU  35 Days -->
    <Item id="twa_book_wasting" name="Pale Surgeon's Notes" mesh="book_b"
          value="5500" weight="1.2" type="Goods">
        <ItemComponent><Armor body_armor="0"/></ItemComponent>
        <Description text="[THE_WASTING] The body is not destroyed all at once. It can be persuaded to fail. Down-Right-Left-Up. Thirty-five days of life. One enemy, fifteen seconds. Six points of health, per second, until there is nothing left."/>
    </Item>

    <!-- Grave Debt  LLDU  45 Days -->
    <Item id="twa_book_grave_debt" name="The Shepherd's Last Reckoning" mesh="book_b"
          value="7000" weight="1.5" type="Goods">
        <ItemComponent><Armor body_armor="0"/></ItemComponent>
        <Description text="[GRAVE_DEBT] The gift does not heal without cost. One of your wounded must go so the rest may stand. Left-Left-Down-Up. Forty-five days of your life. One soldier lost. Every other wound in your warband closed."/>
    </Item>
         Carrying this scroll and reading it permanently unlocks the
         Tyrant Ritual (prisoner sacrifice for youth restoration).
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <Item id="twa_scroll_ritual" name="The Hollow Covenant" mesh="book_c"
          value="15000" weight="0.3" type="Goods">
        <ItemComponent><Armor body_armor="0"/></ItemComponent>
        <Description text="What the gifted are never told: the years do not have to be yours. Those you hold captive carry time inside them. Fear, despair, proximity to death — these ripen it. While you wait, and they wait beside you, the years can pass from them to you. One prisoner. Thirty days of youth. Your honour will not survive it. Your soldiers will know something is wrong. But you will not age. The art does not care what you are. Only what you are willing to do. And if you have no prisoners — consider who else is waiting beside you. The willing carry years too. More of them, perhaps. The cost of that is yours to reckon with."/>
    </Item>

